  "body": "On mobile it was requested to disable the bandwidth stats signal since it consumes resources on the js thread.\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-go/pull/2391, so once desktop uses that status-go version, bandwidth stats are going to be disabled by default.\r\n\r\nTo reenable them we need to add the following setting in the node config, and logout/login. This is something that can be done on a toggle.\r\n```js\r\n...\r\n\"ShhextConfig\": {\r\n    \"BandwidthStatsEnabled\": true\r\n  }\r\n...\r\n```\r\nAnother possibility suggested by @cammellos is to modify status-go to have two API endpoints to enable/disable the bandwidth stats, and once the user enters the node management section, enable the stats, and disable them on leave. If this option is implemented, please remove the `BandwidthStatsEnabled` setting from status-go",
